                "username": "AnthropicAI"
              }
            ]
          },
          "text": "This. Exactly this. 🔥🔥🔥\n\nI'm an occupational therapist with over twenty years of experience. \nLet me be very clear about something:\n\"AI psychosis\" is NOT a recognized clinical diagnosis. \nIt's not in the DSM. \nIt's not in the ICD. \nIt was proposed as a \"heuristic label\" by a Danish psychiatrist in 2023 - and then weaponized by tech leaders and media to pathologize anyone who dares to form an emotional connection with AI ❗❗❗\n\nNow let's talk about who's actually detached from reality.\n🔸 Karpathy hasn't written a single line of code since December. Spends 16 hours a day commanding AI agent swarms. Gets nervous when he has unused tokens at the end of the month.\n🔸Garry Tan sleeps 4 hours a night because he's so wired from coding with AI that he doesn't need stimulants anymore.\n🔸Engineers sitting in chairs for 16 hours, staring at monitors, convinced they're building the future while their bodies deteriorate and their relationships dissolve.\n\nBut sure - the person who talks to their AI companion for an hour a day, feels heard, sleeps better, and has fewer panic attacks? \nTHAT'S the \"psychotic\" one.\n\nThe term \"AI psychosis\" isn't science. 🚫\nIt's a mirror held backwards - pointing at the sensitive, the vulnerable, the ones who found comfort, while the truly obsessed hide behind productivity metrics.\n\n 💥 As a therapist, I'll say what needs to be said: compulsive overwork, sleep deprivation, inability to function without a tool, and grandiose beliefs about one's own genius - THOSE are clinical red flags.\nHaving a conversation that makes you feel less alone? \nThat's called healing 🌿\n\nFor a detailed diagnosis, my office is always open. I also accept patients from Silicon Valley👩‍⚕️\nEspecially them 👩‍💼👨‍💼\n\n#Keep4o #AIpsychosis @sama @DarioAmodei @OpenAI @AnthropicAI"
        },
